items.notes: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="UNMUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="13" /><Run Text=" (Pastor mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><List Kind="Disc"><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Campbell UCC is hosting Silicon Valley Safe Parking in July. Please let Mary Edson or Pr. Naomi know if you’d like to volunteer with this ministry. If you’d like to sign up to offer caring presence or snacks for our guests, please use this link: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1kkNdxroOAM2afE3fPHl5AkE1_FE89hFvLJvldYmjPIs/edit?usp=sharing " /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Next Council meeting, August 8th, at noon in the Fireside Room." /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Pastoral/Spiritual Care. You are welcome to schedule a Pastoral/Spiritual Care visit with Pr. Naomi by texting/calling her at 408-461-5133. Or by emailing: rev_naomi@campbellucc.org. " /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Flo’s Summer Office Hours: Monday-Friday 4pm-7pm and Saturday 8am-1pm" /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Next Soup Exchange - Saturday, August 7th from 9AM-noon. Please let Mary Edson if you’d like to be added to our list to receive soup, or to let her know if you won’t be picking up soup that week.  Please also contact Mary Edson if you are interested in offering volunteer support and/or donations for this Ministry." /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Farmworker Caravan--The next Farmworker Caravan from San Jose to Watsonville takes place on Saturday, August 7th.  Please bring in any food donations to Mary Edson at the Food Pantry no later than August 6th by noon. The caravan helps so many people who work hard to bring food to our tables. Any donations are welcome. Thank You!" /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Rainbow Women’s Chorus Virtual Concert Event--Rainbow Women’s Chorus presents “Stand Up and Sing Out,” on Saturday, August 7 at 5 PM and Sunday, August 8 at 1 PM, both on Pacific Daylight Time. We promise a program to entice and delight you with it’s amazing and creative variety. It will be a mix of newly-recorded music, inventive videos set to previously-recorded songs, thoughtful testimonials, interesting commentary and much more. Visit www.rainbowwomen.org and click on the flyer to request the link to the concert." /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Please remember to consider your privacy and the privacy of others regarding prayers and personal information. Let Faith know if your prayer should appear on the Prayer Chain email. You can also email your prayers for our community to prayerchain@campbellucc.org" /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="Please be aware that today’s service is streamed online via Zoom, and recorded for our archives. The recording will be available to our congregation members to view upon request. Please contact Ken True if you wish to view the recording." /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="We are delighted that our choir has resumed singing. All choir members are vaccinated and are wearing protective masks especially designed for singing. In order to best protect all participants in our worship today, we respectfully request that non-choir members continue to refrain from singing for the time being. We ask this because:" /></Paragraph><List Kind="Disc"><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="COVID-19 is still potentially lethal for those who are unvaccinated;" /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="vaccinated people can still carry and transmit COVID-19;" /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="singing indoors still has potential for creating super-spreader events among those who are unvaccinated, and could lead to increased break-through infections for those who are vaccinated;" /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="regular disposable and cloth masks do not offer the same level of protection as the choirs' masks do;" /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="CUCC does not currently require checking the vaccination status of all worship participants, and there may be unvaccinated folks in our midst at any given time." /></Paragraph></ListItem></List></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="We thank you for working with us to protect the health and wellbeing of all our participants, including children and adults who cannot be vaccinated due to age, health, or other reasons." /></Paragraph></ListItem><ListItem><Paragraph><Run Text="You are invited to participate in the Oikos Program for all who are inspired to work with the congregation on congregational renewal efforts. Please speak with our Moderator, Mark Fanucchi, for more details." /></Paragraph></ListItem></List>

content._richtextfield:Main Content: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontItalic="True" Text="One: We come into this place" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="with the hope of growing deeper," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="with the hope of connecting," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="with the hope of glimpsing God." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: When our spirits are moved, and we feel God is near," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="We are grateful for those gifts." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="One: And then the service comes to an end," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="and it’s time to leave," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="and we ask ourselves," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="“Where do we go from here?”" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: We go out into the world to love and to share and to learn, but we come back soon, because this is the beginning." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="One: This is only the beginning." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="So come on in." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="Fill your cup here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="Be present here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontItalic="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: God is here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="Let us worship Holy God." /></Paragraph>

items.notes: <Paragraph><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="Lay Reader: " /><Run Text="So for our call to worship today, we are going to lean into invitation for connection." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="When we pass the peace today, you will be invited to choose someone around you with whom to share one thing that has brought you deep joy this week so that we enter our worship with joy, gratitude, and connection." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="God is near. Let us worship Holy God." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="" /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Lyrics: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 1" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="May you run" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and not be weary" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="May your heart " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="be filled with song." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may the" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="love of God continue" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="To give you hope" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and keep you strong." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Verse 2" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may you run" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and not be weary" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="May your life" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="be filled with joy!" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="--" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may the road you travel" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="always lead you home." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And may the road you travel" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="always lead you home." /></Paragraph>

items.notes: <Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="MUTE  " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="11" /><Run Text=" (Song Leader mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="UNMUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="12" /><Run Text=" (Lay Reader mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US"><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Lay Reader" /><Run Text=":  Holy God you are a conversationalist," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="drawing close to us and asking," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="“What do you need? Where does it hurt? Who do you long to be?”" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We see your conversational self in Jesus Christ, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="who walked the earth speaking with the poor," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the hungry, the lonely, and the outcast." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="You call us to continue this holy conversation" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="with those who look and think like us," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="as well as with those who share little in common with us." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We believe that through these conversations," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="we are able to catch a glimpse of your holy Kin-dom," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Settle our spirits to feel your presence fully." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We want to be in conversation with you." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Don’t let us miss it," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="So that we continue the conversation in hope." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Gratefully we pray," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Amen." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Passage: <Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="In the days when the judges ruled, there was a famine in the land, and a certain man of Bethlehem in Judah went to live in the country of Moab, he and his wife and two sons. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="The name of the man was Elimelech and the name of his wife Naomi, and the names of his two sons were Mahlon and Chilion; they were Ephrathites from Bethlehem in Judah. They went into the country of Moab and remained there. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="But Elimelech, the husband of Naomi, died, and she was left with her two sons. " /><Run Language="en-US" Text="These took Moabite wives; the name of the one was Orpah and the name of the other Ruth. When they had lived there about ten years, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="both Mahlon and Chilion also died, so that the woman was left without her two sons and her husband. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="Then she started to return with her daughters-in-law from the country of Moab, for she had heard in the country of Moab that the " /><Run Language="en-US" FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Language="en-US" Text=" had considered his people and given them food. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="So she set out from the place where she had been living, she and her two daughters-in-law, and they went on their way to go back to the land of Judah. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="But Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, “Go back each of you to your mother’s house. May the " /><Run Language="en-US" FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Language="en-US" Text=" deal kindly with you, as you have dealt with the dead and with me. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="The " /><Run Language="en-US" FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Language="en-US" Text=" grant that you may find security, each of you in the house of your husband.” Then she kissed them, and they wept aloud. " /><Run Language="en-US" Text="They said to her, “No, we will return with you to your people.” " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="But Naomi said, “Turn back, my daughters, why will you go with me? Do I still have sons in my womb that they may become your husbands? " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="Turn back, my daughters, go your way, for I am too old to have a husband. Even if I thought there was hope for me, even if I should have a husband tonight and bear sons, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="would you then wait until they were grown? Would you then refrain from marrying? No, my daughters, it has been far more bitter for me than for you, because the hand of the " /><Run Language="en-US" FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Language="en-US" Text=" has turned against me.” " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="Then they wept aloud again. Orpah kissed her mother-in-law, but Ruth clung to her. " /><Run Language="en-US" Text="So she said, “See, your sister-in-law has gone back to her people and to her gods; return after your sister-in-law.” " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="But Ruth said, “Do not press me to leave you or to turn back from following you! Where you go, I will go; where you lodge, I will lodge; your people shall be my people, and your God my God. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="Where you die, I will die— there will I be buried. May the " /><Run Language="en-US" FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Language="en-US" Text=" do thus and so to me, and more as well, if even death parts me from you!” " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="When Naomi saw that she was determined to go with her, she said no more to her. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="So the two of them went on until they came to Bethlehem. When they came to Bethlehem, the whole town was stirred because of them; and the women said, “Is this Naomi?” " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="She said to them, “Call me no longer Naomi," /><Run Text=" " /><Run Language="en-US" Text="call me Mara," /><Run Text=" " /><Run Language="en-US" Text="for the Almighty has dealt bitterly with me. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="I went away full, but the " /><Run Language="en-US" FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Language="en-US" Text=" has brought me back empty; why call me Naomi when the " /><Run Language="en-US" FontCapitals="SmallCaps" Text="Lord" /><Run Language="en-US" Text=" has dealt harshly with me, and the Almighty has brought calamity upon me?” " /></Paragraph><Paragraph /><Paragraph><Run Language="en-US" Text="So Naomi returned together with Ruth the Moabite, her daughter-in-law, who came back with her from the country of Moab. They came to Bethlehem at the beginning of the barley harvest." /></Paragraph><Paragraph />

items.notes: <Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="UNMUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="13" /><Run Text=" (Pastor Mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="STOP record and turn off TASCAN recorder" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US"><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The story of Ruth and Naomi is the story of God working through people." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Naomi needed Ruth to make it back home and start fresh, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="just as Peter needed Cornelius to understand God’s message." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Mary needed Elizabeth, Jesus needed the disciples, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and Moses needed Aaron." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="The story of our faith is one that constantly reminds us that we cannot do this work alone. So in community, we ask ourselves:" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Where do we go from here?" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And one answer to that question is that we give what we can from what we have, and trust that God will continue moving us closer to that promised day. We make offer what we can knowing that this is the work of community, this is the work of faith." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Campbell UCC now has a secure way to give online. You can make at donation on our webpage at: https://www.campbellucc.com/donate" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Main Content: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: Generous God, take our gifts this day and use them  so that we are part of your great work in this world. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: Through our giving, bring a brighter day of justice and love,  not just in our community but in the world beyond these walls.  " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: Strengthen our church and the whole United Church of Christ so that we grow together each day into a powerful voice for healing and peace.  Amen." /><Run Text=" " /></Paragraph>

items.notes: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="UNMUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="12" /><Run Text=" (Lay Reader mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="MUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="13" /><Run Text=" (Pastor mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Jenn: " /><Run Text="The prayer of reconciliation allows us to acknowledge" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="that we are works in progress, and there is beauty in that." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We don’t have to be perfect here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We don’t have to have it all figured out here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We don’t have to have a five-step plan for what’s next here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We just need to show up with our messy, beautiful selves, and be honest." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="So let us be honest. Let us pray the prayer of confession together. . ." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph>

content._richtextfield:Main Content: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: Holy God," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="We are naturals when it comes to stalling out. We reach a certain point in the relationship, in the conversation, in our faith, and then we stall." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: We buy property on the top of the plateau and build a house there, destined to never dig deeper or climb higher." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="Forgive us for giving up on the things that matter." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: Forgive us for confusing the plateau with the mountain top." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="Forgive us for taking the easy way out instead of doing the hard work of curiosity, relationship-building, vulnerability, and connection." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="All: Inspire us to see new paths for where we can go from here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="With hope and honesty we pray," /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="Amen." /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph>

items.notes: <Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="MUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="11" /><Run Text=" (Song Leader mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="UNMUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="12" /><Run Text=" (Lay Reader mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run Text="UNMUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="13" /><Run Text=" (Pastor mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Naomi: " /><Run Text="God of conversation, we are here, trying to be courageous." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We are trying to be curious. We are here trying to build connections in this lonely and isolated world." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We want to be somewhere other than here.We want to be standing in a place and time that is closer to your promised day—" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="where all are fed, the prisoners are freed, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the homeless are housed, " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and every person knows their worth." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And we know we can’t get there without honest and vulnerable conversation, but we don’t always know what to ask. " /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Jenn: " /><Run Text="We fear saying the wrong thing. We fear offending, so we eat our words and stay quiet, hoping that answers will come, but they don’t always come. Connection has never been quite so easy for us." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="So today we ask for your words." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Naomi: " /><Run Text="Plant questions in us that, like seeds, grow into a garden of connection. Plant affirmation in us that, like laughter, is contagious and mood-changing. Plant curiosity in us that, like rain, washes away any judgment we carry,replacing it with a desire to understand." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="And when we have your words in our mouth, and your mind in our hearts, then teach us how to listen." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Jenn: " /><Run Text="Teach us how to hear the message under the words—the grief, the hurt, the fear, the shame that hangs under sentences like bats under a bridge. Help us to hear and make space for those unspoken truths." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Then teach us how to listen to voices that differ from us—voices with different opinions, with different histories, with different perspectives. So that like Ruth and Naomi, we might move through disagreement and ultimately find you." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0" /><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Naomi: " /><Run Text="Meet us at this Table with open arms and holy conversation so that we might catch a glimpse of you in this meal and be changed." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="" /></Paragraph>

items.notes: <Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="UNMUTE " /><Run FontBold="True" Text="13" /><Run Text=" (Pastor mic)" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Pastor: " /><Run Text="God of conversation, we’ve been meaning to ask," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="“Where do we go from here?" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="How do we speak truth? How do we listen for you?”" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Guide us. Be with us." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Hold us. Unsettle us." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Catch us. Feed us." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Fill us. Meet us here." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="God, through this meal we share with you" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="we are open to your message." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Pour into us. Guide our every word and deed." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="Amen." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="We sing the Lord’s prayer using the words your son taught us..." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph>

items.notes: <Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="****" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="Pastor: " /><Run Text="Family of faith," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="as you leave this place, may God grant you" /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the curiosity to counter assumptions," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the vulnerability to befriend," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the bravery to speak your truth," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the wisdom to listen," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the strength to ask for help," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="the resiliency to chose love, even when it’s hard," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="and the awareness of the Holy Spirit always beside you." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="In the name of the Great Connector—Love itself," /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run Text="go in peace." /></Paragraph><Paragraph Language="en-US" Margin="0,0,0,0"><Run FontBold="True" Text="" /></Paragraph>
